messages.message:
:cypress-spin: Summary of 6/10 - 6/14 Cypress On-call :slack_call:
• Lots of tests failed on aihub-sandbox over last weekend (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C029ZG026GZ/p1718036710618509?thread_ts=1718015245.619479&cid=C029ZG026GZ) because of a change to `useAIHubUsageSummary` and the switch of the org from commercial to enterprise. This change did not affect CI runs since the org used there stayed as commercial.
• crafting-aihub was broken for most of Tuesday because of a failed db migration (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05L87V014J/p1718136100969969?thread_ts=1718135733.338919&cid=C05L87V014J)
• on Wednesday, we were back in business and fixed several tests! :couscous: to all!
    ◦ @Udit fixed (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/58567) a deployment API intercept so that `reviewer-dashboard` would pass
    ◦ @Weiming Wu fixed (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/58595) `view-my-hub` to check only projects created during the test
    ◦ @danny.lan fixed (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/58309) some flakiness for `aihub-extraction`, `edit-existing-app`, and `run-public-app`
• Throughout the week, some CI runs failed because of timeouts or login issues (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CSY11CK7T/p1718312979777939).
    ◦ For timeouts, reruns would often solve the issue. If there were multiple CI runs with failures only caused by timeouts, we force-merged the PR (example (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/57736)).
    ◦ Login issues seemed to occur in PR sandboxes that have been up for a long time across crafting-aihub deployments. Deleting the sandbox and triggering a rerun resolved the issues.

:x: Summary of top 20 failed tests this week (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/analytics/top-failures?branches=%5B%5D&browsers=%5B%5D&chartRangeMostCommonErrors=%5B%5D&chartRangeSlowestTests=%5B%5D&chartRangeTopFailures=%5B%5D&committers=%5B%5D&cypressVersions=%5B%5D&flaky=%5B%5D&operatingSystems=%5B%5D&runGroups=%5B%5D&specFiles=%5B%5D&status=%5B%7B%22label%22%3A%22Passed%22%2C%22value%22%3A%22PASSED%22%7D%2C%7B%22label%22%3A%22Failed%22%2C%22value%22%3A%22FAILED%22%7D%5D&tags=%5B%7B%22disabled%22%3Afalse%2C%22label%22%3A%22ci%22%2C%22labelProperties%22%3A%7B%22color%22%3A%22%23dadade%22%7D%2C%22suggested%22%3Afalse%2C%22value%22%3A%22ci%22%7D%5D&tagsMatch=ANY&timeInterval=WEEK&timeRange=%7B%22startDate%22%3A%222024-06-10%22%2C%22endDate%22%3A%222024-06-14%22%7D&viewBy=TEST_CASE)
• @Udit `manager-dashboard` failed 20% of the time and is flaky 8% of the time, often because of an off-by-one check (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CSY11CK7T/p1718312743893519) in the UI
• @Udit `reviewer-dashboard` failed 20% of the time is and is flaky 7% of the time, sometimes because of an off-by-one check in the “Time remaining” column (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/11281/test-results/fb9c2376-e519-434b-9db4-9e1ea0aad53f/replay?att=1&isFlaky=%5B%7B%22value%22%3Atrue%2C%22label%22%3A%22Flaky%22%7D%5D&ts=1718305102093.8909) and sometimes because it can’t find documents for a run id (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/11313/test-results/273c5134-5def-4f22-862d-6fdc90cac9dc?isFlaky=%5B%7B%22value%22%3Atrue%2C%22label%22%3A%22Flaky%22%7D%5D)
• @Aayush @Subash `converse-project-crud` failed 16% of the time, often in the part for deleting a Converse project
• Failed because of timeouts
    ◦ `results-table` 22%
    ◦ `field-editor` 21%
    ◦ `documents-grid` 17%
    ◦ `nested-field-editor` 17%
    ◦ `members-crud` 15%
    ◦ `drives` 12%
• Failed because of login issues
    ◦ `oauth-crud` 19%
    ◦ `aihub-classification` 13%
• Failed because of timeouts and a frontend build issue that couldn't be reproduced (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C059K24M35E/p1718310714887759?thread_ts=1718304126.338869&cid=C059K24M35E) (resolved after deleting the PR sandbox)
    ◦ `aihub-extraction` 23%
    ◦ `aihub-data-types` 20%
    ◦ `aihub-refinement` 17%
    ◦ `aihub-results-table` 15%
    ◦ `aihub-refinement-udf` 15%
    ◦ `edit-deployment` 14%
• Failed because of timeouts and because the app wasn’t set up in the new account
    ◦ `advanced-apps` 14%
    ◦ `run-app` 12%
:ghost: Flaky tests this week (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/analytics/flaky-tests/1712c8eb-fa44-ebf0-095e-2139a236af33-56593df9-27a8-2958-6a39-9d84c1166612?branches=%5B%5D&browsers=%5B%5D&chartRangeMostCommonErrors=%5B%5D&chartRangeSlowestTests=%5B%5D&chartRangeTopFailures=%5B%5D&committers=%5B%5D&cypressVersions=%5B%5D&flaky=%5B%5D&operatingSystems=%5B%5D&runGroups=%5B%5D&specFiles=%5B%5D&status=%5B%7B%22label%22%3A%22Passed%22%2C%22value%22%3A%22PASSED%22%7D%2C%7B%22label%22%3A%22Failed%22%2C%22value%22%3A%22FAILED%22%7D%5D&tags=%5B%7B%22disabled%22%3Afalse%2C%22label%22%3A%22ci%22%2C%22labelProperties%22%3A%7B%22color%22%3A%22%23dadade%22%7D%2C%22suggested%22%3Afalse%2C%22value%22%3A%22ci%22%7D%5D&tagsMatch=ANY&timeInterval=WEEK&timeRange=%7B%22startDate%22%3A%222024-06-10%22%2C%22endDate%22%3A%222024-06-14%22%7D&viewBy=TEST_CASE)
• The tests that are medium flaky (11%-50% of the time) are flaky because of timeouts
• `aihub-validation-library` @Arjun and `aihub-validation-udf` @Serena are flaky 8% of the time, often because the validation result does not come back in time
• @Jessica `create-deployment` is flaky 5% of the time, often because the downstream integration was not created successfully (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/11331/test-results/ce2ceccf-8260-4bf2-ae7e-8514a258eb97/replay?att=1&isFlaky=%5B%7B%22value%22%3Atrue%2C%22label%22%3A%22Flaky%22%7D%5D&ts=1718383808242.218)
